Text.SourceString: Oh… Hi there...
My name is <NPCName>Rafael</>.//<portrait=concerned>Umm...//<portrait=normal>I’m one of the blacksmiths here in Starlet Town.
There is so much trash around this island.//I go to the river? Trash.//I visit my niece at the beach? Trash.
Some people. *sighs*
There is so much trash around this island.//I go to the river? Trash.//I visit my niece at the beach? Trash.
Some people. *sighs*
We get a lot of work from the town.//Putting up decorations and stuff.
I don’t mind cleaning up the town. I grew up here.//This whole town is my playground, and I want to take care of it.//I would appreciate it if you can also keep it clean.
I should start gardening. I’ve been relying too much on nature lately.//I’ve only been gathering mushrooms, and I’m getting tired of those things…
Yuck.
I should start gardening. I’ve been relying too much on nature lately.//I’ve only been gathering mushrooms, and I’m getting tired of those things…
Yuck.
I should start gardening. I’ve been relying too much on nature lately.//I’ve only been gathering mushrooms, and I’m getting tired of those things…
Yuck.
Our shop has been the same since Mom and Dad retired.
Oh, it’s not bad or anything, but I wouldn’t mind an upgrade, you know.
I have all these ideas for weapons, but I can’t make them just yet.//<portrait=concerned>Our current furnace isn’t up to it.
Once we upgrade the furnace, hopefully we can make more advanced weapons and tools.
I have all these ideas for weapons, but I can’t make them just yet.//<portrait=concerned>Our current furnace isn’t up to it.
Once we upgrade the furnace, hopefully we can make more advanced weapons and tools.
Uhh…? What’s wrong?
Umm… After work, I usually just cook dinner or something. I don’t know…//<portrait=sad>Did that answer your question?
No, I don’t really go to the Tavern.//I go to the lake sometimes if I need to relax.
My brother and I can upgrade all kinds of tools.//You just need to bring us the ores.
And some compensation for our labor would be nice.
We only accept money as a form of payment. Sorry.
The cemetery is very quiet… So is the lake.//It’s my ideal place to read horror novels.
Yes, I read other books too.
I like peace and quiet.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, you too? Well, we’re kind of the same, then. Is that why you moved into your grandparents' farm?
I get it, though. It’s hard to get peace and quiet when you work next to a massive furnace all day.
Favorite sushi? Umm… I like sushi in general.//So, as long as it’s fresh, any kind is fine by me.
You fish a lot, don’t you? You must eat a lot of fish.
We get our ores from the cavern… The one located up north of the forest.//If you don’t see the ores you need, I suggest you keep digging.
When you upgrade your tools, they’ll change color slightly.//It depends on the upgrade material.
Don’t be alarmed. It’s completely normal.
There’s nothing I like more than a good horror movie.//It keeps you on the edge of your seat.
Okay, maybe trying out a new weapon.//<portrait=happy>That stuff is creepy too.
Oh no, I haven’t had the time to visit the cemetery.//<portrait=normal>Maybe next Monday.
<NPCName>Pablo</> spends a lot of time in the garage. He seems to ALWAYS be calibrating his TV.
It sounds good to have a big empty place in the middle of nowhere, to be honest.
I like peace and quiet.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, you too? Well, we’re kind of the same, then. Is that why you moved into your grandparents' farm?
Something in common, eh?
I still have some work to do for the day so I can't go to the Inn today.//I usually visit my niece at the inn on Sunday. I get to see the twins too.
The air is different at the beach. It’s saltier.//<portrait=annoyed>And a bit sticky.
Maybe I can live there full time and walk to work.//<portrait=surprised>But it would be a waste of money.
We’re closed today. The store also closes early on Saturdays.//Family day for us.
You can sell metal bars, and they go for more than raw ores.
Business is booming. We need more space.//Or better tools.
Another customer? Coming out of the woodwork these days, aren’t ya?
What can I do for you?
I use my forge, my bellows, and my own two hands.//Sometimes, though, I wish I had a little extra help.
Aside from <NPCName>Pablo</>, of course.//He’s great.
I wish I could spend more time with my niece, <NPCName>Valentina</>.//My work here keeps me so busy, though.
My work keeps me so busy. I wish…
No. No wishing. You want something?//You work for it.
Have you heard the legends about magic on this island?//<portrait=annoyed>Bunch of silly hand-waving and mumbling, if you ask me.
Hopefully I’m wrong… ’Cause that would be really cool.
I love creating weapons. One day I hope to make something truly special.//Something people will remember me for.
There’s more ore than what you find down in the cavern. Incredible stuff.//Some might say mythical…//<portrait=annoyed>Course, most of that is probably just old stories.
Still, stories have to start from somewhere, right? Maybe there’s a mote of truth in ’em.
I tried carpentry, but it’s not for me.//I can make small things or fix a cabinet, but building a whole house is too much.
<NPCName>Joko</> and <NPCName>Dinda</> are top-notch carpenters, anyway.//I don’t think the market here is big enough for another carpenter, even if I wanted to be one.
I like creating weapons more than upgrading tools.//We have limited resources for making weapons, but that won’t stop me from going all out.
There are weapons that I’ve made...weapons that I can’t sell, because they failed the safety test.//<portrait=happy>But maybe I can show them to you sometime.
Hillside is a great spot to live in. Just far enough from the town.//Unlike the woodlands… That’s a tad too close to everyone.//<portrait=annoyed>Whatever, though.
I tried carpentry, but it’s not for me.//I can make small things or fix a cabinet, but building a whole house is too much.
<NPCName>Joko</> and <NPCName>Dinda</> are top-notch carpenters, anyway.//I don’t think the market here is big enough for another carpenter, even if I wanted to be one.
Argh.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, hey! Didn’t see you there.
You can check out our shop if you need some new weapons or boots.//I make most of them myself.
Yes, sometimes <NPCName>Pablo</> does, too.
Open pretty much every day, but the store closes early tomorrow.//<portrait=happy>And we’re closed on Sundays.
We’ll keep working nonstop if we don’t keep a schedule. Not good…
<NPCName>Valentina</> is a great kid. I feel like <NPCName>Antonio</> is a bit too hard on her sometimes.//But I’m not a parent, so…

She’s the daughter of my cousin, <NPCName>Antonio</>.//Yeah, she calls me and <NPCName>Pablo</> “uncle,” even though we’re not her dad’s actual brothers. It’s kind of a thing in our family… I don’t know.//It’s not weird at all for me…
I like creating weapons more than upgrading tools.//We have limited resources for making weapons, but that won’t stop me from going all out.
There are weapons that I’ve made...weapons that I can’t sell, because they failed the safety test.//<portrait=happy>But maybe I can show them to you sometime.
Yeah?
Sorry, I’m a bit busy. I need to fix this real quick.
Legend has it you can make some really incredible stuff, with the right ore.
There are a lot of explorers coming to town these days.//A few come into the shop, looking for weapons or tools. Just like you.
Right…right! Tourists.//Some of ’em have some pretty wild stories…
Have you ever heard of the Ironeye Hammer? Legend says it’s a magic hammer that forges items by itself!
I don’t believe in it, of course. But imagine how much time I’d save if it were true…
According to legend, the Ironeye Hammer also speaks to you while it works!//<portrait=happy>I wonder if it knows any jokes.
I’d be a fool to put my trust in the Ironeye Hammer.//It works by itself, but the legends don’t say whether it’s a good worker.
Does it get tired? Does it take personal days?//<portrait=surprised>The legends are mysteriously silent on these issues.
I’d best get back to work. My head’s been in the clouds too much these days.
It’s been a couple days since my explorer friend left to find tevandium. I can’t wait until he comes back!
Do you think the explorer found the tevandium yet?
I wonder if it’s real. Tevandium, I mean.//The explorer said he’d seen it, but if it’s mythical, who knows what he really saw?
I hope it’s real. I have big plans.
I would have expected the explorer to be back with the tevandium by now. I hope he’s okay.
The Ironeye Hammer isn’t the only tool you can make with tevandium. Just the most famous.//<portrait=happy>I can’t help but let my mind wander.
The Greatstone Amulet, the Firestarter’s Axe…this could change the entire shop.//<portrait=happy>The entire island!
What if the explorer decided to keep all the tevandium for himself?//I just realized that he never told me where the cave was, exactly…
Maybe I shouldn’t have paid half up front.
I hate to be pessimistic, but I’m starting to doubt the explorer is going to return with that tevandium, <PlayerName>$player</>.
<NPCName>Pablo</> is my older brother.//We look a bit alike, don’t we?
No, just us. We don’t have any other siblings.
I smelt ores all day sometimes. *sighs* So please don’t mind my dirty clothes.
It’s easy to lose track of time. Smelting ores is such a mundane job.//My body immediately goes into autopilot.
You know, my parents were once farmers just like you. They said that you need to be strong to be one.//Kudos to you.
Yeah, sure, I can see myself as a farmer.//Didn’t we talk about this already?
I can’t believe people throw out perfectly good food around here.//What a waste.
I smelt ores all day sometimes. *sighs* So please don’t mind my dirty clothes.
It’s easy to lose track of time. Smelting ores is such a mundane job.//My body immediately goes into autopilot.
I’m visiting my niece tomorrow. It’s good timing to go and visit the beach, isn’t it?
I also help out at the inn, doing odd jobs. Changing light bulbs and all that. The twins never asked me to do anything… They don’t need my help, but I don’t mind doing it.
These days I feel like I’ve lost my wits. I need to get my head out of the clouds.
Maybe I need a vacation. Get away from the forge for a bit.
I know what happened, <PlayerName>$player</>. I figured it out. I sent that explorer to his doom!
That’s the only explanation for why he hasn’t come back. What a fool I’ve been!
You want something done, do it yourself.//I should have just paid him to tell me the location of the ore, instead of making him get it for me.
I’m sure that explorer will be back with my tevandium any day now.
These days I feel like I’ve lost my wits. I need to get my head out of the clouds.
Maybe I need a vacation. Get away from the forge for a bit.
Purifying the tevandium will be hard, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m not even sure I can do it. But I have to try!
I’m still having a hard time removing the impurities from the tevandium.
If I can’t remove them, I’m wondering if I can just go ahead and make the Ironeye Hammer anyway.
Is it hot outside, or is it just me?
Summer is a little uncomfortable for me. I prefer Winter.//<portrait=concerned>Uh…um…maybe Fall.
I’m looking forward to the hot pot at the Cherry Blossom Festival.//<portrait=annoyed>Not looking forward to fishing the vegetables out of my portion, though…
The cherry blossoms are really pretty this year.
I’m glad the birds are out and about, but sometimes I wish they’d pipe down a bit. Just a bit.
Are you busy, <PlayerName>$player</>? I hear farmers are usually really busy in Spring.//Do you need help?//<portrait=concerned>I don’t think I can help, though. I’m a little busy myself. Sorry…
I wish Winter could be longer, but new horror films are usually released in Fall… So, that’s something to look forward to with the new year.
I just want to stay outside all day…//I need some fresh air.

I rented this horror film yesterday… <Italic>Alakazam</> – a classic, I think. I watch it every Summer.//<portrait=annoyed>Anyway… I haven’t had a chance to watch it. I think I’m gonna need to pay late fees again.*sighs*
Working in front of the furnace in Summer is something else… //I can tolerate it just fine in other seasons, but Summer is just unbearable.
<NPCName>Pablo</> keeps inviting me to the tavern, but I keep telling him I just want to be inside.//<portrait=sad>It’s too hot to do anything… I don’t like it.
Sorry I’m such a bummer, <PlayerName>$player</>. I think it’s just a Summer thing… I hope.

How’s your Summer so far? Mine’s okay. I spend a lot of nights watching horror films in my room.//No, no. I don’t have a TV in my room. I have this tablet… Anyway, never mind. It’s small and not very fancy.
I can hear the bugs singing at night outside my window.//Yeah, it’s nice.
Maybe I can install some ceiling fans in time for next Summer.//<portrait=annoyed>All I do is fan myself in bed using old newspapers… Makes me feel like a salmon being smoked.
<NPCName>Valentina</> can play in the sun the whole day – in this heat.//I don’t know… I don’t think it’s healthy, right?//What do you think?
I feel like the grass right now. Withered, yellow, lifeless…//Maybe I should drink some water.
I’m looking forward to <NPCName>Betty’s</> homemade mooncakes. They’re always the highlight of Fall for me.
I wonder what films are coming out this Fall.//I like the ones with jump scares. Just nice classic horror films with ghosts.//<portrait=concerned>Um…
Gonna spend the weekend nights watching Fall films with ghosts…//Even better, ghosts from folk tales. What are you gonna do?
It’s still too warm to spend all day in front of the furnace.//<portrait=normal>But at least the wind is pretty cool.
I wonder what Beluga Bay will be showing at this year’s Harvest Festival…
Fall has to be my favorite season.//I’m lucky to live here. It’s easy to go out and enjoy nature whenever I want to.
Winter is nice… I like it.
I think I have the ingredients to make ramen tonight.//Gonna eat it in my room and watch funny videos on my tablet.
I forgot to close my bedroom windows the other day before going to work…and my bed froze.//Well, yeah… No, it wasn’t actually frozen. It was just really cold.//<portrait=sad>Um…sorry.
If I get too hot, I just step outside and let the Winter air cool me down.//I can do that now…because it’s Winter.
Are you warm? Make sure to stay warm, okay?
This Winter is a little dry.//My hands hurt if I wash them too much. But it’s nothing unbearable.//It’s okay…
Winter coats are hard to wash.//They’re very thick. They take a long time to dry.
I like the cold wind. It feels good against my face after a whole day exposed to the hot furnace.
I’m bringing some fish to the potluck. I’m not a big fan of vegetables.
Umm… I meant the Cherry Blossom Festival.
Yes?
You can turn canola into oil using an oil maker.//I don’t think you can buy oil makers, but you can easily make one yourself once you have the blueprint.
For some reason mosquitos don’t bite me. Isn’t that weird?
I brought some edamame for <NPCName>Valentina</> yesterday. I keep forgetting that she hates it.//I hope she doesn’t hate me now.
I would probably fish if I didn’t have to keep my parents’ shop open.
That would be a very different life for me. I would get a lot of fresh air.
Eating something cold like cold fish or ice cream would be good right about now.
The majority of the trash here drifted in from the sea. Can you imagine what it’s like where this trash came from?
I need to go to the clinic this week… For personal business.
Heh heh… What? You look happy today.//It kind of makes me happy to see.
Today is the last day of Summer, yet the heat doesn’t want to let up.
I’m not doing anything special today. It’s just another Thursday for me. What about you?
I’m not doing anything special today. It’s just another Thursday for me. What about you?
I’m not doing anything special today. It’s just another Thursday for me. What about you?
I like the cold wind. It feels good against my face after a whole day exposed to the hot furnace.
I hope <NPCName>Stephen</>’s claw grows back real soon so he can go back to exploring the sea.
Oh! Umm… <NPCName>Stephen</> is <NPCName>Macy</>’s adopted lobster.
My parents aren’t natives of Coral Island.//They came here when they were young, with two of my uncles, from Dulca Island.
Dulca Island is very far from here.//<portrait=normal>Growing up, our parents used to take <NPCName>Pablo</> and me there to see our grandparents. But, you know, not too often.
Winter is a great time to upgrade your tools. That way you can be prepared for a busy Spring.
Ever since you moved here, <NPCName>Sam</> has much more variety in his store.
I like the cold wind. It feels good against my face after a whole day exposed to the hot furnace.
Oh! Umm… <NPCName>Stephen</> is <NPCName>Macy</>’s adopted lobster.
Hot air balloon rides terrify me…but I would like to try someday.
And…my stomach hurts thinking about it.
I’m feeling a bit nervous about <NPCName>Bree</>’s dinner party tomorrow.
I’m afraid I might say the wrong thing and ruin people’s dinners.
I hope it starts raining soon.
The walking path could stand to be rinsed off.
I hope it starts raining soon.
The cemetery is starting to smell. It could use a rinse.
I hope it starts raining soon.
The bushes need some water.
The rain makes for some relaxing white noise in the background, don’t you think?
*yawns*
I feel awkward talking here.
The rain makes for some relaxing white noise in the background, don’t you think?
*yawns*
Oh no! I need to dry off my boots. Mud everywhere!
Oh well.
A storm like this blew our roof off one time.//<portrait=sad>We had to relocate for a few days while it was being fixed.
I’m sure your cabin would be fine, though. Don’t worry.
It’s storming outside.
It’s storming outside.
The rain is relaxing, isn’t it?
It’s a bit harder to walk when it’s raining, though.
I tend to spend too much on things I don’t need at the fair.
They make a stop here every year before going down south.
Yeah, he’s part of it. But I think <NPCName>Ben</> stays here, in Coral Island.//<portrait=normal>Only travels once a year.
The snow helps me build up a resistance to cold weather.
You can find all sorts of minerals in the cavern.//If you dig deep enough, there are plenty of diamonds and such. Beware of monstrous bugs, okay?
Calling it a day and going to rest. I’ll continue tomorrow.
Don’t slip going home.
We have some snow boots at the shop.
Yeah? Is something the matter?
I’m just cleaning up a bit of moss on the stones.
Sometimes I come here to read a book. It’s nice and quiet.//<portrait=normal>What are you doing here?
Some of the books here are very odd.//<portrait=annoyed>I think I read something about a flying dog one time.
It was probably <NPCName>Alice</>’s.//<portrait=normal>That girl is out of this world with her theories.
<NPCName>Taco</> lived here for several weeks.//Then <NPCName>Suki</> brought him over to <NPCName>Luke</>’s for a playdate, and the puppy refused to come back.
So <NPCName>Taco</> lives there now.
I don’t take orders outside of the shop.//If you want to get your tools upgraded, come by to the shop tomorrow, will you?
You can always tell when my brother walks into a room.//Any room, really… Conversations seem to get livelier, don’t they?
When <NPCName>Pablo</> tells jokes, my parents laugh harder, you know… Simple stuff like that.//<portrait=concerned>People don’t notice, but I do.
Upgrading a tool, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Getting the right weapon can really help with slaying certain monsters.
In my downtime, I sometimes mine for some ores in the cavern to make weapons.//You can always count on our store if you need ores right away.
I need to go back to work.
Oh, umm… I came here for some tacos.//I’m not in the mood to cook anything.
I’m going back to work after this.
It feels good to be outside every once in a while.//<portrait=normal>The shop is way too hot sometimes.
I don’t usually come here, but it’s <NPCName>Pablo</>’s birthday today, so I just came out for a celebratory meal.
I never notice how loud it is in here. Wow!
I should go home soon. I feel exhausted.
<NPCName>Pablo</> and I went over to the inn and had a quick dinner with our niece, <NPCName>Valentina</>, to celebrate her birthday last week.
<NPCName>Pablo</> gave her a geode because he thought she would enjoy finding treasures, but I guess not…
